%% Diagram: 3D Secure 2 frictionless vs challenge flow
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Cardholder
    participant M as Merchant
    participant DS as 3DS Server (PSP)
    participant DSV as Directory Server (Visa / MC)
    participant ACS as Issuer ACS

    C->>M: Submit payment
    M->>DS: AReq (browser / device data, txn context)
    DS->>DSV: Routed AReq
    DSV->>ACS: Routed AReq
    ACS->>ACS: Risk-based authentication

    alt Frictionless (~95% of low-risk traffic)
        ACS-->>DSV: ARes authenticated (no challenge)
        DSV-->>DS: ARes
        DS-->>M: Authenticated, liability shift to issuer
        M->>M: Authorize via acquirer
    else Challenge required (PSD2 SCA / high risk)
        ACS-->>DSV: ARes challenge required
        DSV-->>DS: ARes
        DS-->>M: Need challenge
        M-->>C: Render CReq (biometric / OTP / push)
        C->>ACS: Complete challenge
        ACS-->>DS: RReq result
        DS-->>M: Authenticated (or failed)
        M->>M: Authorize or decline
    end
